You are only updating adminMetadata. Following are some descriptions and examples of different ways to use the adminMetadata property in a description. Use these as a reference when updating adminMetadata in the description.

## adminMetadata
The adminMetadata field contains information about the record itself.

| Property | Definition | Value type | Repeatable |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
contributor |	Contributors to this resource description.	See Contributor for subproperties |	Yes	|
event	| Events in the history of this resource description.	| See Event for subproperties	| Yes	|
language | Languages, scripts, symbolic systems, and notations used in this resource description.	| See Language for subproperties	| Yes	|
note	| Other information related to this resource description. See admin metadata note types.	| See Description for subproperties	| Yes	|
metadataStandard	| Descriptive or content standard(s) to which this resource description conforms.	| See Standard for subproperties	| Yes	|
identifier	| Identifiers associated with this resource description. See all identifier types.	| See Description for subproperties	| Yes	|

### Language of record

The language or languages used in the record description.

```json
{
  "adminMetadata": [
    {
      "language": [
        {
          "value": "English",
          "code": "eng",
          "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/iso639-2/eng"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### Creator of record

The institution responsible for creating the record.

```json
{
  "adminMetadata": [
    {
      "contributor": [
        {
          "name": [
            {
              "code": "CSt",
              "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/organizations/cst",
              "type": "organization",
              "source": {
                "code": "marcorg"
              },
              "role": [
                {
                  "value": "original cataloging agency"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### Metadata standard

The standard used in constructing the record description.

```json
{
  "adminMetadata": [
    {
      "metadataStandard": [
        {
          "code": "rda",
          "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/descriptionConventions/rda",
          "source": {
            "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/descriptionConventions"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### Other information

Additional information about the record.

```json
{
  "adminMetadata": [
    {
      "note": [
        {
          "value": "human prepared",
          "type": "record origin"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```
